<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
<div class="panel on" id="panel-howit">
  <div class="blue-note">
    Think of Google like a giant phone book. When someone types "house cleaning near me," Google looks at every cleaning business in the area and picks the ones that look the most trusted and relevant. <strong>The more places your business shows up online, the more Google trusts you and the higher you appear in results.</strong> This plan shows exactly what words people are typing and what I am doing to make sure Nina's business shows up when they do.
  </div>

  <div class="insight-card">
    <div class="insight-icon">📍</div>
    <div class="insight-title">Google Maps is the most important place to show up</div>
    <div class="insight-text">When someone types "cleaning service near me," Google shows a map with three businesses at the very top before any websites. This is called the Local Pack. Getting Nina into those three spots is the main goal. Her Google Business Profile (the listing we already set up and optimized) is what gets her there.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="insight-card">
    <div class="insight-icon">🔑</div>
    <div class="insight-title">Words people search are called keywords</div>
    <div class="insight-text">A keyword is just the words someone types into Google. For example "house cleaning near me" is a keyword. The more times we use those same words on Nina's website, Google listing, and posts, the more likely Google is to show her business to that person. Think of it like raising your hand every time a teacher asks a question.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="insight-card">
    <div class="insight-icon">📊</div>
    <div class="insight-title">We use a tool called SEMrush to find the best keywords</div>
    <div class="insight-text">SEMrush is a professional tool that tells us exactly how many people are searching for any word or phrase every single month. It also tells us how hard it is to compete for that word. We use this data to focus on the words that will bring Nina the most customers in the shortest amount of time.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="insight-card">
    <div class="insight-icon">📝</div>
    <div class="insight-title">Google posts keep the listing active and visible</div>
    <div class="insight-text">Google lets businesses post updates, offers, and news directly on their Google profile. These posts show up when someone searches for Nina's business. Posting every week tells Google that the business is active, which helps it rank higher. It is like updating your social media but it goes directly into Google search results.</div>
